citeinfo.title: SJRWMD Public Water Service Area Boundaries (PWSABs)

descript.abstract: With population expected by 2020 to increase to nearly 5.2 million and total water demand for SJRWMD projected to increase to about 1.85 billion gallons per day These data becomes one part of an integrated water resource allocation and water supply decision-making process. In significant portions of the priority water resource caution areas, alternative water supply sources will have to be developed to meet future needs while sustaining water quality, wetland and aquatic systems, and existing legal uses. Groundwater alone cannot meet all future water supply needs. Development of alternative sources of supply will require cooperation among the water supply utilities, SJRWMD, and the Florida Department of Environmental Protection. These data represent one of the water supply development componets of The St. Johns River Water Management District's (SJRWMD) Distrct Water Supply Plan (DWSP)
descript.purpose: To map public water supply service areas within the SJRWMD that have a public supply CUP permit allocation component from ground and/or surface water sources.
descript.supplinf:
October 2012: Removed THRESHOLD attribute
July 2010: Added attribute UTILITY CATEGORY - Small, large or other with small being any utility that has a CUP allocation < .1mgd, large >= .1mgd and other being nursing homes, military bases, churches etc.
August 2010: Added attribute PermitID - ID asscociated with PWSABs outside the District
July 2011: Permit ID deleted and PWS_ID added PWS_ID was added mainly to add potable water service areas that do not require a CUP but use potable water.

DATA LINEAGE REPORT
DATA LAYER: pwsab (public water service area boundaries)
NOTE: Name was changed from SAB (service aerea boundaries) to PWSAB in June 2003
LOCATION: x:/wsm/library/public_supply/data/gis
NAMING CONVENTION:
DATA TYPE: polygon
MAP TILE:
DISTRICT COVERAGE STATUS: Complete
SOURCE SCALE: Varied. ~24,000
DATUM: 1983 HARN
MAP PROJECTION: UTM, Zone 17
MAP UNITS: Meters
LAST TEXTFILE UPDATE: 6/26/09
MEDIA OF SOURCE: Varied. Paper Maps, Digital Files,
DATE OF SOURCE MATERIAL: 1991
TIME INTERVAL COVERED: 1991-present
CREATOR ORGANIZATION / INDIVIDUAL:Kimball Lloyd,Inc.3001,SJRWMD CONTACT: Steve Brown, GISP Bureau of Water Supply 386.329.4427 sbrown@sjrwmd.com
DERIVATION METHOD FOR DATA: Preautomation compilation method: (hand drawn maps digitized to coverage)
DATE OF AUTOMATION: Complete version available 06/09/98
UPDATE SCHEDULE: When will the data be re-collected? Varied. As new data is obtained from utilities.
EXPLANATION OF PROCEDURES USED TO DIGITIZE/SCAN/TRANSFORM ETC. THE DATA: The PWSAB coverage is a culmination of Kimball and Lloyd's WS_DATA boundary coverage(s)(1991) and extensive research and edits by Wes Harrel, Francis Mizell(1992-1997),3001 (1997-98), Kevin McNinch (1998-99), Steve Brown (2000-present). 3001 was contracted (1997-98) by the Division of Water Supply Management(WSM) to QA update/revise/edit the original coverage as a part of their water use population contract.
SUPPLEMENTAL INFO: In the beginning (pre 1991) the service area boundaries existed mainly as hand drawn on paper maps as a result of the CUP application process. In 1990-91 the Division of Water Supply Management contracted with Kimball Lloyd, Inc. Engineers,Architects,Surveyors, Vero Beach FL 407.562.4112 who produced a technical document/report/work product "DELINEATION OF PUBLIC WATER SUPPLY SERVICE AREAS AND WASTEWATER TREATMENT PLANTS - FOR SJRWMD - WATER USE PROJECTIONS" JUNE, 1991. Part of their study/research resulted in the identification (from researching SJRWMD CUPs) 487 Water service areas within the SJRWMD which were converted/digitzed into ARC/Info coverage(s) (WS_DATA)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
